metadata.name: Harbour Dusk
metadata.description:
Edition: 1/1
Artist: Céline Pannetier
Size: 4333 × 2889
Location: Barcelona
Date: 2023
Camera: Fujifilm X100S


One thing about birds and humans in the city… I stand mesmerised by this weird relationship we built.
Winter afternoon, cold weather, walk on the boardwalk. 
Kids and adults alike, local and tourists alike, feed the birds. Seagulls and pigeons fight for the crumbs. 
I am standing there, and illuminate the scene with my solid, full blown flash.

About Céline Pannetier: 
She is a French Photographer based in Barcelona. She is a Street Photographer whose work was finalist in several Street Photography International Festivals. She exhibited her work in galleries in NY, Paris, Barcelona and Rotterdam.
She also works as Events and Congress Photographer and recently started to explore Creative Food Photography for which she was finalist both of the Sony World Photo Award in 2022, and the Siena Intl Photography Award in 2021.
